Prolific comedian Jim Gaffigan has booked two shows in Tampa for Oct. 15, and the performances will be filmed for his next comedy special. Tickets are on sale at the David A. Straz Jr. Center for the Performing Arts to see the Emmy-winning comedian, actor, writer, producer and bestselling author. He is one of the most successful comics in the world, known for his unique brand of clean comedy that largely revolves around his observations on life. He will perform at 7 and 9:30 p.m. in Morsani Hall. The Straz Center notes: “These performances will be filmed and recorded for Jim Gaffigan’s next comedy special.” The Indiana-born comedian has produced 14 comedy specials. Since 2017, he has put out one per year. Tickets for The Fun Tour are $39.75-$125.75 at strazcenter.org or by calling 813-229-7827.